The paper deals with image representations and classification, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed pooling mechanism involves re-weighting per-patch statistics, which is a machine learning technique and could place the paper in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing pooling operations and proposes a novel mechanism, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The experiments involve image classification benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves similarity measures and re-weighting, which could place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
